                            <comment id="81083" author="utopiabound" created="Fri, 4 Apr 2014 20:41:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Merged to master aacc286fe0575d455794121264a612c29ffb7740&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="80017" author="haasken" created="Fri, 21 Mar 2014 17:30:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oleg, vvp_vmpage_error() handles limiting dirty page discard warnings to one message per file.  Isn&apos;t that right?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch worked correctly in my testing, printing only one message per file.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="80016" author="green" created="Fri, 21 Mar 2014 17:20:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well, the thing is we definitely need to rate-limit this, but be more smart about it.&lt;br/&gt;
Multiple pages from teh same file warnings could be safely merged and rate-limited.&lt;br/&gt;
It&apos;s all the different files that we should print about for sure.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="80012" author="haasken" created="Fri, 21 Mar 2014 17:07:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Uploaded a patch here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/9752/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/9752/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
